        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-12T12:06:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I added more detail to the doc.  \"from-to\" is only simpler in the linear-history case; otherwise you *have* to think in terms of \"reachable from B but not A\" or things make no sense.  So callers need to be aware that in the common case this just means \"give me the commits between A and B\" but that branches and merges can cause it to include other sub-graphs.",
      "parentUuid": "d8c835c0_05defc55",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 426,
        "startChar": 58,
        "endLine": 427,
